<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Hmmm I too am more inclined to agree with Ravn. Tho i3ullseye, I have to say your suggestions have been very helpful to my playing a sorc so far  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Some of your suggested changes are necessary, but not sufficient. <P>1.  Matter spec.  I agree this needs to be fixed...BUT this will only help relatively NEW sorcs, not those of us who have already put most of our points into mind and body.  Laudable to create a new line of characters with some ability in matter, but we who have already placed our points need survivability too.  I'm not going to go back and re-level another sorc to 36...I'll quit first.  <P>2.  If indeed we are supposed to be masters of crowd control, I for one would really like to actually be able to DO that.  As it stands in RVR the stun is way more useful than the mez for doing that.  Stun is faster to cast, it can be cast on ppl with low health, it cannot be healed and you can inflict additional damage and not break the stun.  Only disadvantage to stun is duration is less.  Well in the rvr battles I've been in once I'm stunned, I'm dead...so shorter duration seems not to matter much.  Crowd control in rvr currently belongs to the stunners.  <P>Suggestions:  First...make stun healable! Stun implies a shock to the system and mez does not...so also make mez NOT healable.  Secondly...concentration spells should be broken by mez AND stun...shouldn't be able to concentrate after either has been done to you.  3rd make mez range equal to that of bolt casters...ya damage is their forte so they should have good range...but mezzing is ours and we deserve the same consideration.  REMEMBER mez alone does very little...if I'm alone and mez someone orange and above, my choice is usually to just run...that's not true for a wizzie who can finish someone off with two bolt spells.  Yet the wizzie gets realm points and I get nothing for using my spec'ed ability.  Pets in rvr are hard to find and often lower level...plus when you die as often as we do in rvr, it's REALLY hard to hold on to one for any length of time...so we really can't count on them for aid.  Plus, unlike pve we have no way to keep aggro on them, we can't even use our tanks to shield us...once we are targeted by an archer, we are pretty much dead, even WITH bladeturn.  <P>So if you think mez changes are unbalancing, consider that an archer can kill a sorc usually in 2 shots, maybe 3 at outside, and since their range is so long and they have stealth, there is really nothing the sorc can do about it.  When they do that, the archer gets realm points.  BUT as a sorc, there is NOTHING I'm able to return the favor to.  So if the perceived problem with mez is that other players will get frustrated because they have to wait for up to a minute to play again, consider the sorc who is killed without opportunity to respond almost all the time, and has to either get rez and recover (longer than one minute I assure you) or release and head back to from the bindstone(sometimes up to 15 minutes to get back in the action).  If one minute mez is frustrating, I ASSURE you 15 is more so.  <P>Giving longer range on mez would at least give us a ghost of a chance of surviving an archer snipe...tho I don't think I'd still survive it very often because of difficulty in targeting the archer.  Still, if it were an option I'd consider it more fair.  As it is, I'm a sitting duck for archers or anyone with greater range.  <P>I'm also a sitting duck for stun because I can start casting my mez, and after I do it, a stunner still has time to run in close start casting, get his stun off and interrupt my mez...so much for crowd control.  Ya, maybe i can use quickcast, and I do as often as possible...but resists are getting pretty common, and on a purple now, the mez can be gone before I even get my quickcast back, assuming it's not resisted.  <P>I can't emphasize enuff that unlike stun, mez is NOT instant death for the mezzed. A tank gets ONE HIT on a mezzed character before he can defend himself...NOT true for stun, I've taken 4 and 5 hits while stunned without being able to respond.  Sorcs will still have a hard time killing rvr folk even if the mez takes, plus since a whisper cancels and it can't be cast on things that have taken appreciable damage, at the current point in time if you wanna do crowd control I'd suggest a character with stun.  <P>Finally, a disguise option would be an EXCELLENT addition to the sorc mind spec line for rvr...kudos on that suggestion.  Let us target a mob or player an cast the spell to take on that character's  or appearance for 15 minutes or so.  Idea works very well for making the sorc a much more desirable rvr class since right now we are simply sitting ducks.  I REALLY like this suggestion, and it's not as powerful as stealth, but gives us SOME options.  <P>Finally, I think charm should also affect players just like it affects mobs.  There's no logical reason it shouldn't.  We already lose amnesia in rvr and most of the usefulness of confusion.  Here's what I think charming players adds:<P>First of all charming a character in rvr would be rare, given the requirements that already exist for charm.  Second, if we could get the charm off, we'd be able to take a hostage...which I think would add immensely to rvr tactics.  What I would do to prevent the complaints about a sorc taking control of someone's character for hours on end is introduce a suicide command so that the charmed player can suicide and die at any time while charmed.  This is less nasty than archers currently have it against sorcs, since they can send sorcs to the bindstone almost automatically without giving the sorc a choice.  That way, the sorc can actually send the player against his friends in a battle...and the player would have the choice...hope that the sorc bites it before he does appreciable damage to his friends, OR suicide to prevent doing that damage.  I think this addition alone would make the sorc a way more popular character without unbalancing anything too much just because the effect is so cool.  Remember, charms in rvr would be a bear to get off, would only apply to players your level or under, and sending against a mob to kill the player should also result in no loss of con or xp...with the message "you have recently been charmed, you lose no xp or con"...the same fix that prevents you from getting xp for killing a recently charmed critter. <P>Tequitus (36 sorc)
</FONT>
