Few things...<P>The question asked has no bearin on new or old sorcerors, it was merely which line needed more meat added to it.<P>It was NOT which ones needed fixed.<P>It was NOT what would sorcerors like to see added to the class.<P>A disguise type spell will likely never happen. I woudln't mind seeing it, but the rogues have precious few unique abilities as is. the only other types that will get shifting will be Berserkers becoming animals and such. Only the rogue types will have true disguise or stealth. I don't think we will ever see spells that can duplicate this and move in on their territory.<P><BR>And I also see us NEVER getting charm that works on other PCs. I would love to see it, but it just isn't likely to happen. Just being stunned and helpless is frustrating enough, what kind of outcry would there be if we could take total control of the target. Now they have to actually watch as we use them to fight. If we don;t get them killed, then what? They stay transfixed, staring at their monitors while we have total control of their game?<P>Charm woudl also be a one shot kill. This one spell would take them ENTIRELY out of the combat. <P>Just not gonna happen....<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
