<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I think the best way would be somewhere between Ravn and i3bullseye.  Even though Ravn has some great suggestions, if all of Ravn's suggestions were taken, we would be far too powerful.  Also those changes would take far too much programming and Mythic wont be doing that any time soon.  I can see that i3bullseye is striving towards balance but sometimes goes to far in weakening the class.  My view can be summed up in four changes in this order and number one should be addressed immediately:<P>1) Fix mez for PvE and PvP and make CC effective and reliable.<BR>2) Sorcers need a use when CC is not needed<BR>3) Fix matter line<BR>4) Fix charm<P>The first priority should go to Mind and CC because that is the largest benifit that we bring to a party.  We should be compared to a Healer because they are much more powerful than us.  A group with a Healer will always win against a group with a Sorcerer because they have faster casting times and insta casts and two crowd control lines, both mez and stun compared to our one.  Also Healers get clarity so can cast their spells with almost no mana cost.  Healers are also much more sturdy and can tank so can get much closer and can cast without having to worry about collapsing like a fragile sorcerer.  Not only that but when diminishing return runs out, a Healer can still stun or fall back into a tank or cleric position while a Sorcerer simply has to run away.  In RvR, the Sorcerer should be balanced against the Healer, our Midguard equivelant.  Sorcerer should have faster or equivelant cast to Healer and should have more powerful CC, after all we are a pure caster and sacrifice armor, absorbtion, hp and any melee ability.<P>Sorcerers are suppose to be the CC class and we need to be able to do CC effectively and reliably in a group.  When we fail, it causes our death and other group deaths and we are a failure in the eyes of the group.  We need a way to recover if we get a resist.  Maybe Mez resist should not cause monsters to aggro to us immediately.  Maybe when they wake from mez they should not b-line straight towards us.  Maybe sorcerers should have a unnotice self buff which causes monsters to not notice them (so they are never aggroed to us unless the monsters make a difficult skill check).  Maybe we need a stun line.  Lastly, two sorcerers in a group should be able to work together.  As it is now, two sorcerers can easily step on each others toes and render mez shortlasting or useless.  A mezhappy cleric can do the same thing.  Mez should not be so dangerous and Sorcerer should not have to die 10 times more often then other group members.<P>Sadly, theurgist are now better CC than us and Cabalists, Wizards and Smite Clerics are catching up to us in CC ability.  My cleric is starting to hear "We need a theurgist to handle the adds" in groups now.  Two theurgists in a group are infinitely more effective at CC than two sorcerers and a theurgist can always take away crowd controling from a sorcerer because pets break mez.<P>Second priority is to give sorcerers a use when mez is not necessary or is used up.  I think that the easiest way for this is to make the debuffs effective.  I have done testing and casting DD is always more effective than debuff.  DD's shorten the fight more causing the tanks to take less damage and does more damage on the monster.  It doesn't matter how big the group is wether you are soloing in a group of 2-3 or in a 8 person group.  I have tried against blues to purples.  I have tested debuffs in all those cases and they are always inferior to chain casting DD's.  We always end up taking less damage and killing the monster faster when using straight DD's, but our DD's are not even very good.  When fighting places where CC is not required, Sorcerers need to be able to still contribute to a group.<P>The Matter line needs improvement and anyone that does not admit this does not have any points in Matter.  Don't be selfish, think of the gimped Matter sorcerers for once, they need some help.  Improving the matter line should be third priority.<P>Fourth priority should be fixing charm so we can charm more pets and fixing our runspeed buff so that our pet does not lag behind, cause aggro and get us and our group killed.  This would help alleviate the pet shortage at some levels and would be an additional CC tool.<P>Lastly, I have heard reports that mid purple's hits cancel bladeturn, so bladeturn is useless in a group fighting mid-purples.  If this is true, maybe it needs to be examined.  What level of purples hit through it?  Does this get worse or better as level increases?  Do we need more powerful bladeturns at higher levels to negate this?<P>Thanks i3bullseye, you are doing a great job straightening out our class.  I might not agree with all your decisions, but it is great that we have someone examining the class that cares about it and who has the complete picture in mind and is trying to evolve the class in a way that we don't get too powerful and then nerfed again somewhere down the line.
</FONT>
