Umm Ravn....this is Dark Age of Camelot, not everquest. We are not an Enchanter but a hybrid of an enchanter and necro. Some of your points are off base I believe. Reduced Mez resistance.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><BR>Remove the variable duration nonsense, interrupts, diminishing returns and resists are enough to contend with.<P>Faster casting on Mez spells across the board. That Mez does me no good if by the time I cast it the Mob is already beating on the cleric.<P>Increased Mez range.<P>Instant cast Mez spells on timers for emergencies.<P>Point Blank AE Stuns (that do NOT break Mez).<P><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I honestly dont want any of these spells. Would they be nice? Yes. Are they needed? No. We are not Wizards that need long range nukes. We are not Midgard Healers and need the Dazzle line ( AoE stun from EQ). I dont need insta cast Mez nor faster casting times. Ever hear of the quickcast feature? How much range do you need in a dungeon? <P>This is how I do it. Puller calls 3 inc, I target the rear mob and cast AoE mez. I then proceed to back up a bit and wait for the tell tell signs that Mez is about to break ( you kow the ones where the mob acts like he is non aggro and stands up straight). Then either cast Mez or an AoE again. I cant tell you how many times people that have never played with a sorcerer before start to love me. As long as everyone pays attention to me calling out next target ( dont most sorcerers do that?), then all is good.<P>This is especially nice now that we have bladeturn spell. Notice how mobs almost always seem to come directly at us 1st? That quickcast is a life saver.<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><BR>Group Desirability Suggestions<P>Concentration based Endurance Regeneration bufs.<P>Concentration based Power Regeneration bufs.<P>Concentration based Agro multiplier bufs.<P>Concentration based Agro reduction bufs<BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>We are not Bards,Minstrels or Skalds. These are some defining songs for those classes. We do not need to leech them for that class. <P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR><BR>Realm Vs Realm Suggestions<P>Realm points for Mez and Debufs.<P>Invisibility and Detect Stealth spells.<P>Make our spells work in RvR (Amnesia, Confusion, and maybe even a limited form of Charm).<P>Illusions. I would love to be able to masquerade as one of the enemy, or baring that I&#8217;d settle for being to be able to disguise the fact that I&#8217;m a sitting duck (Illusion Armsmen).<P><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Why not give everyone Invis and Dectect Stealth? This one seems to be coming from left field. Dont need nor want this spell. Again, this is infriging upon the Rogue classes defining ability. Want Detect Stealth? Group with a Rogue or Scout.<P>Hace you even tried confusion in RvR? I have chain casted this before in small group hunts. Really pisses tanks,archers and casters off. What does it do in RvR? Stops and Inturrupts ALL forms of combat. Archers fumble with thier bows, casters cant cast that spell they were trying to get off. And the spell is cheap and fast casting.<P>No Illusions, this is not EQ. <P>Only valis point I see is maybe RP's for debuffs and Mezzes as that can turn the tide of a battle. But that would probably mean that if we mezzed to derail a train in some dungeon or to save someones life, we would be exp leeching ( probably built into the code)<P><BR>Nioron <BR>Sorcererss<BR>Guinievere Server
