ose the sorcerer with the idea that we will be the best in crowd control and that is our niche. As sweeping changes are made to class abilities as a whole, it is becoming apparent that we are NOT necessarily the best at Crowd Control, and these changes actually do not address the initial imbalances they were intended for, but only weaken the other classes grouped into the category affected by the change. <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>Whole heartedly agree, this was a good paragraph.<P>      <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">quote:</font><HR>Man, tough room here&#8230;. I heartily recommend reading all future posts like this twice before flying into a fit of rage! <HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>I read your post twice, and I did not fly into a fit of rage.  I merely tried to give constructive criticism in as polite a fashion as I could manage in my agitated state.  Trust me, when I fly into a fit of rage you&#8217;ll know about it.<P>You need to stop treating every contradicting view as a personal attack.  I have no quarrels with you, I merely disagree with how your handling some portions of your job as a class TL.  If my comments are annoying you then let me know.  I&#8217;ll stop wasting my time trying to help you better the class we all enjoy playing.<P><I>Edit: The class we use to all enjoy playing.</I><P>Syth,<BR>33rd Level Malefice,<BR>Pellinor
