Read the posts and I have to say, I totally agree with Ravn.  Sorcerers are weak and not equipped to do their job.  Up until about level 30, I was doing the crowd control (with a lot of help) because we naturally assumed that Sorcerers would be better at it.  If any of you know a minstrel or cleric who really knows his class, you'd realize they can do crowd control a lot better than we can.  They are better prepared to take the hits and have the spells to help them with crowd control.  Clerics have insta mez, stuns, more hp and better armour to take the hits.  Minstrels don't get insta mez, but they can keep a mob out indefinitely and they have stuns to help them do their job.  A good minstrel will also be able to twist a heal or manasong in  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P>RVR.  Haha.  Only recently started doing RVR but here's what some of my experiences have been like so far.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">  Went to Emain last night.  First fight was against hibbies.  Tried to mez.  Out of range.  Stepped in closer and began casting.  &lt;soandso&gt; nukes you to death in two nukes.  Later on that night, we had about 20 middies at the Albion wall.  They were all pretty clustered together.  I thought "ooooh, perfect opportunity to mez them".  I hit my ae mez button.  Out of range.  Stepped in closer and began casting and then I got "you have been mezzed".  Some troll stepped in and then proceeded to whack me to death  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">  Don't get me wrong, I've been able to mez a small party when we surprise them.  Of course, they are usually grey - yellow only. :b  <P>We definitely need reduced casting time.  I would definitely love to get stun, but I doubt we'll ever get that.  If we can't get stun, we need to be able to quickcast mez as many times as we need to.  And to keep it from being so overpowering, I guess you could keep increasing the casting cost every time you quickcast it.  &lt;shrug&gt;  I personally could live with that because right now, all my power goes to nuking because the minstrels and clerics in my guild are doing the crowd control. <P>Aeriana<BR>36 Sorceress<BR>Punching Bag<BR>Gawaine<P>--------------------<P>Aeriana<BR>TnT
