I have come to the same conclusion as most the people on this board: namely, that our crowd control abilities are useless in situations where they should be effective. Whilst Confuse and Amnesia may work, people rarely notice me casting Amnesia to save a caster, and Confuse has such a ridiculous effect it generally results in the tanks going after the target and getting more aggro in the process, as the creature runs around the room and warps through walls. I normally get told off for casting this, even if it can save lives.<BR>Now, I am currently in the Catacombs with my level 30 Sorcerer, and my mezzes are very effective. I get hardly any resists because, presumably, the mobs are mostly orange to me. At the same time, the healers have gone to the Barrows at 26 (ok, perhaps a slight exaggeration) and are gaining experience at a much faster rate than me. I go to the Barrows and, if I am lucky enough to get an invite (because I bring nothing tangible to the group), I quickly become a costly liability. I can't mezz anything (aside from the occasional red mob in the first room), my debuffs don't appear to help in the slightest (target goes down very quickly anyway with a few tanks on it and Wizard nuking), and you have read my comments on Confuse and Amnesia.<BR>My point is, why should I be only be able to effectively mezz targets which give me pretty lame experience, whilst people who are the same level as me and playing tanks, for example, can hit targets I can't mezz?<BR>I was getting compliments in the Catacombs for my abilities to mezz, but when I go the Barrows at 30 I quickly look like a bad player, or at the very least a completely usless class.<BR>I know that everyone playing a Sorcerer thinks we should be able to mezz higher targets, or else how are we supposed to group effectively with people the same level who can take on those targets?<BR>Something is clearly wrong here. Either we should be able to contribute or they shouldn't be able to take them down so quickly.
