kamdar,<P>Im sorry but the difference between a level 26 Sorcerer and a level 33 Sorcerer is immense.<P>You are at the turning point now, as you get closer and closer to level 30 you will begin to see what Ravn and others are so infuriated about.<P>I havent played in over a week, im having so little fun ( make that NO fun) with my 36 Sorcerer.      <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"> <P>As for bullseye, I appreciate the job your trying to do, but I have to agree with ravn in as much as, the class doesnt need levitate or a single target speed spell. those are at best tertiary additions to our class.<P>The class takes a massive dive in playability/viabilty and fun post level 30, we need to be able to survive red and purple mobs beating on us for more than 1 second ! that is our primary weakness in PvE. As far as RvR goes, we as a class are a joke ! Ive tried many many times out there to join in the fun ! If I can get close enough to AE mezz, it usually spells the end for me a few seconds later.<P>Sorcerers are cannon fodder out there. The vast majority of our spells either do not work or are in the process of being nerfed.<P>Ask yourself this question....<P>How many other classes go into RvR and lose their primary ability  ? answer, none ! <BR>The nerf to charm (inability to charm players in RvR)  is the equivalent of an armsman going into RvR using only a shield because his sword/axe or polearm doesnt work in RvR,  they wouldnt stand for it and neither should we.<P>Mythic needs to be told straight, give us a viable role in RvR.<P>As for charming enemy players, its a MUST, all that needs working out are the details. I would propose a short duration charm, perhaps 20 seconds and then a freeze on recast for perhaps 10 minutes, details to be discussed. Charm, thats what we are about, or at least the vast majority of us. I had no idea when I chose a Sorcerer that I wouldnt be able to charm enemy players, I was really looking forward to it.<P>I'd change classes in a heartbeat if I had the chance ! thats how bad we are overall, thats why no one plays the class, least not in any significant numbers ! <P>I humbly suggest that next time you are asked a question that requires a specific answer, that you use ome creative license.<P>FORGET matter line altogether. Think to yourself, well 99% of Sorcerers are mind/body spec'd therefore I think either one of them needs something extra.<P>Any of the two fundemental spec lines would have done. I think by choosing matter you fell into a well designed trap.<P>If they now add to the matter line, myself and 99% of level 25+ Sorcerers are going to be hurting because we didnt spec that line.<P>So in closing, we need to be able to survive melee encounters for a few more seconds in PvE and we need our fundemental spell line to work in RvR OR be given a DAMN good replacement in the mind or body spec lines.<P>Some good ideas here from several posters.<P>I know you (bullseye) dont have to post here, but if you dont get a consensus from your piers, whats the point in your telling mythic anything.<P>Lets stop dancing around with tertiary spells and get our basic needs addressed. Thats post level 30 needs !
