<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
As a Sorc on Palomedies, I do not find it hard to get into groups.  In fact, I and my brethern are often sought after as group members ( once the requsite tanks and healers are in place of course).<P>So, I find the general statement of non-groupage somewhat silly.<P>Just for the record im a 2/3 mind/body spec. <P>I will include some observations from this weekends play in the Catacombs ( im lvl 27 ) where I went from lvl 24 to 27.<P>1.  No problem getting a group at all.  Sometime had to decline offers.<P>2.  When pulling Tribunes ( mostly low purple and later on red ) single target mez landed 100% of the time except when the mob was enguaged in close melee.  I used "pre-targeting and was much more successful in lading mez on mobs inbound than those already in combat. <P>3  Multiple target mez (ae) mostly successful on purples and reds ( and 80% roughly ) on oranges, same effect on engaged mobs vs. enrout.<P>4.  Was able to land mez on mobs who were less than 10% damaged ( eyeballed the damage vs the xp dot to guage..not accurate but best I could do.<P>5.  Debuffs didnt matter in combat as the mobs were often dead quickly.<P>6.  Same as #5 for dots.<P>7.  Confuse and amnesia were party-savers in every case.  Used only when the mob got onto the healer(s).  Amnesia resisted more when mob was in combat than not.  Confusion rarely resisted except by purples ( nasty ones ).<P>I found myself able to mez the adds, and keep mobs off the healers.  I did have my personal body guard ( thanks Rem!) who was assigned to keep mobs off me.  The primary spells used were Mez, Confuse, Amnesia, AE mez and Mind DD. ( which gets big adds against undead it seems).<P>In every case where we had a bad pull ( more than 3 purples ) if I died ( this only happened 3 times all weekend ) the party died.  If I was protected we lived with only one or two tank deaths ( Brave lads! ).<P>Perhaps dividing the spells into 2 categories will help in the discussion or analsys, Party use spells and Soloing spells.<P>One further note:  Those players who have played Eq with an Enchanter understand not to swat mezzed mobs and how the "parking lot" style of fighting works.  Generaly they have /assist macros set up and stay on one mob then get the next etc.  I does take some time to introduce this to UO players or those <P><BR>Dyyphyz Stonehead
</FONT>
