Getting through to me won't help.<P><BR>Log onto pendragon and play some there. log some time there. petition problems there. that is the control environment, and if the few sorcerors who play there are taking all these changes in stride, and still soloing effectively, then nothing is going to change. If you can;t get an even level pet, and rip through blues almost non stop, soemthing is wrong. if you can't hunt 2 or 3 targets at once for nice group bonuses, you are NOT using all the tools at your disposal.<P>Read some of the online strategies people are posting on the web. try different spell combos. try different equipment.<P>Our target is to reliably solo blue MOBs for xperience at any given level. thats it, not yellow, not orange because we have a pet. Now with a pet we CAN do orange, and can fairly reliably do yellow. But the pet healing, the Xp split, and the downtime makes this NO MORE EFFICIENT THAN HUTNING RAW BLUES. This is not something we can cry about and change it, this is by design. Noone can hunt as many blues at once as us for an extended period of time. this generated a very healthy group bonus for us and actually makes us solo faster than most AT TARGET.<P>I think maybe it is I who is not getting through to most people here. The generally accepted idea of where classes should be power wise is NOT the mathematically engineered place that they fall in game. If we are intended to run at 22Mph in game, it doesn't matter if yout hin we shoudl go 25Mph, it isn't going to change.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
