<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
!3ullseye:<P>I think that your original post addressed the question posed to you, and it has some good suggestions for the matter line, which IS our most useless spell line at ths point.<P>That having been said, I think one of the most vexing problem I personally am facing as a sorceror today is in RvR.  As others have commented (and as you have noted), it's just plain tough.  Although our AOE debuffs and mezzes are theoretically useful, it is difficult to survive long enough to use them.<P>Anyway, apart from the somewhat useless matter line and mezzing concerns of the class, I hope that we can become more viable in RvR.  I think that making the "confuse" spell work on other players -- for a much shorter duration -- might be a step in the right direction, and I hope that perhaps you could pass this suggestion along if the opportunity presents itself.<P>EDIT: I think the "soloing" aspect of the thread arose because that's the way Mythic balances the classes/game -- by gauging how well you solo blues.  A viable balancing strategy?  Not entirely sure, but I think not.<P>EDIT #2: I think that it's tough to expect your paying customers to invest significant time playing a game on a "test" server.  There needs to be some incentive for playing there, and there currently is not.  I think that it makes more sense to test as much as you can for bugs on the test server, then release the patch and get the balance feedback from the community as a whole.  Perhaps if that is the model used, it makes sense to select a number of individuals from all servers who are willing to provide feedback and compile the information they provide on the changes.  That might provide a representative sampling of how the changes affect balance, while reducing the millions of posts that Mythic would otherwise need to read through.<P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
